cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on deep learning algorithms and their efficient training in distributed environments. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of computation resources in data centers, which suggests a possible fit with cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification, object detection, and semantic segmentation, which are all related to computer vision, indicating a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for adjusting the learning rate, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, suggesting a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the effects of stochastic momentum, which is a common topic in neural networks, indicating a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
